<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb8256bcc-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s3596"><num value="3596">§ 3596.</num><heading> Regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Office of Personnel Management shall prescribe regulations to carry out the purpose of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb8256bcd-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/95/454/tIV/s404/b">Pub. L. 95–454, title IV, § 404(b)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-13">Oct. 13, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1167">92 Stat. 1167</ref>, § 3595; renumbered § 3596, <ref href="/us/pl/97/35/tXVII/s1704/a/1">Pub. L. 97–35, title XVII, § 1704(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1981-08-13">Aug. 13, 1981</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/95/756">95 Stat. 756</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
